@Osiris1975 For the sorting: there's no code I can see in your view to do the sorting. Take a look at the [sortable.py](https://github.com/plumdog/flask_table/blob/master/examples/sortable.py#L28) example. You have to do the sorting of the items yourself. All the table class does for sorting is to handle the display of the sorting links in the headers.

And for the pagination, the table doesn't know anything about pagination, that's why in my snippet before both the table and the pagination object get passed to the template. Then you can use the pagination object for pagination things, and just `{{ submissions_table }}` for the table.

Hope that helps!

